return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531311\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qky1665702876251.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qky1665702876251.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qky1665702876251.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qky1665702876251\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Installing and Configuring Character Sets\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface needs to be installed with the correct character set for a specific language and platform. Settings in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">.asn</span> determine which character sets are used. Some settings are common for all types of character sets. Others are for specific types of character sets.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"qky1665702876251__context_w8538ab1b5b1_w8539ab1b5_w8540ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"qky1665702876251__topic_d28691e1_d28692e1_d28693e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qky1665702876251__p_d28694e1_d28695e1_d28696e1\">Platform Requirements:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qky1665702876251__li_d14627e1_d14628e1_d14629e1\">Microsoft Windows—a single-byte character set\n                  can be installed either on the localized operating system (for example, Central\n                  European Uniface on a Czech Windows system, Arabic on a Arabic Windows) or an\n                  English Windows that has a multi-language setup (called an enabled version). <p class=\"p\" id=\"qky1665702876251__p_d28697e1_d28698e1_d28699e1\">For double-byte character sets, a localized\n                     Windows is required. For example, install Japanese Uniface in a Japanese\n                     Windows system, Simplified Chinese in a Simplified Chinese system, and Korean\n                     in a Korean system.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"qky1665702876251__note_w8541ab1b5b1b1b3b1b3_w8542ab1b5b1b1b3b1_w8543ab1b5b1b1b3_w8544ab1b5b1b1_w8545ab1b5b1_w8546ab1b5_w8547ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Ensure that the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Locale</span> of the operating\n                     system is set to the desired language.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qky1665702876251__li_d14630e1_d14631e1_d14632e1\">Linux and Unix platforms—the installed character set should match the language of the operating system.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qky1665702876251__li_d14633e1_d14634e1_d14635e1\">EBCDIC-based platforms—the installed character set should match the language of the job. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kwm1665702876321.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kwm1665702876321.html\" title=\"To install Uniface on iSeries, you need to be familiar with the iSeries environment and system setup. You require training equivalent to at least the IBM i system operator workshop.\">iSeries Installation Requirements</a>.\n                    </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"qky1665702876251__topic_d28700e1_d28701e1_d28702e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qky1665702876251__p_d28703e1_d28704e1_d28705e1\">To install and configure a character set:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qky1665702876251__li_d14636e1_d14637e1_d14638e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Install Uniface, as appropriate for your platform. During installation:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"qky1665702876251__li_d14639e1_d14640e1_d14641e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">When prompted for the directory in which to install Uniface, avoid using non-ASCII characters in directory names.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"qky1665702876251__li_d14642e1_d14643e1_d14644e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Character set selection screen, select the generic character set you want to install.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qky1665702876251__li_d14645e1_d14646e1_d14647e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qky1665702876251__p_d28706e1_d28707e1_d28708e1\">In the assignment and initialization files, set the configuration settings as appropriate.\n On Microsoft Windows, the Uniface installation program generates settings for the selected character set. On other platforms, you need to ensure that configuration settings are appropriately set.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qky1665702876251__p_d28709e1_d28710e1_d28711e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wvf1665702876540.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wvf1665702876540.html\" title=\"The .ini and .asn settings are used for all character sets.\">Settings for All Character Sets</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iqm1665702876023.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iqm1665702876023.html\" title=\"You can specify the layout orientation of the application. This is important for the bidirectional character sets such as Arabic and Hebrew. To use Japanese Gaiji characters, use $GAIJI setting. Use $NLS_SORT_ORDER to select the sorting order for a double-byte character set.\">Settings for Specific Character Sets</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vfj1665702877040.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuration Settings for Installable Character Sets on Windows</a><p>These are the contents of the usys.ini and the usys.asn files generated by the Uniface installation program for each installable character set in Windows platform.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531311\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531311\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Installing and Configuring Character Sets Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Installing and Configuring Character Sets Uniface needs to be installed with the correct character set for a specific language and platform. Settings in the .ini and .asn determine which character sets are used. Some settings are common for all types of character sets. Others are for specific types of character sets. Platform Requirements: Microsoft Windows—a single-byte character set can be installed either on the localized operating system (for example, Central European Uniface on a Czech Windows system, Arabic on a Arabic Windows) or an English Windows that has a multi-language setup (called an enabled version). For double-byte character sets, a localized Windows is required. For example, install Japanese Uniface in a Japanese Windows system, Simplified Chinese in a Simplified Chinese system, and Korean in a Korean system. Note: Ensure that the Locale of the operating system is set to the desired language. Linux and Unix platforms—the installed character set should match the language of the operating system. EBCDIC-based platforms—the installed character set should match the language of the job. For more information, see iSeries Installation Requirements . To install and configure a character set: Install Uniface, as appropriate for your platform. During installation: When prompted for the directory in which to install Uniface, avoid using non-ASCII characters in directory names. In the Character set selection screen, select the generic character set you want to install. In the assignment and initialization files, set the configuration settings as appropriate. On Microsoft Windows, the Uniface installation program generates settings for the selected character set. On other platforms, you need to ensure that configuration settings are appropriately set. For more information, see Settings for All Character Sets and Settings for Specific Character Sets . Related Links Configuration Settings for Installable Character Sets on Windows These are the contents of the usys.ini and the usys.asn files generated by the Uniface installation program for each installable character set in Windows platform. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}